Constructor
-A constructor is special type of method
-init-(double under line)
-it is used to initialize object of class

use-
1.initialize object
2.throughout class use kar sakte hai

types of constructor--
1.Default constructor
2.user defined constructor--{a.Parameterised .b.Non parametrised


Difference between method and constructor-
method
1.give any name
2.return values
3.can take any parameter /argument
4.use object to call/class to call

Constructor
1.Name is fixed def_init_(self)
2.will not return any value
3.can take any parameter
4.will call at the time of object creation itself
--------------------------------------------------------------
Static method not used for constructor
bcz static method no need to create object and if not created object then constructor not called.